company_description:
SimpleCiti Holdings is a dynamic and innovative holding company dedicated to revolutionizing the real estate industry. Based on the principle of simplicity and efficiency, SimpleCiti embodies the vision of creating streamlined and effective solutions across various sectors within the real estate domain. Our mission is to make complex processes simple and accessible, driving value and growth through our diverse portfolio of businesses. Our Brands:
SimpleSPACES: Specializing in multi tenant industrial properties, SimpleSPACES offers flexible leasing solutions for industrial warehouses, ensuring tenants have adaptable and efficient spaces for their operations. SimpleBricks: Focused on development, SimpleBricks is committed to creating high-quality, sustainable real estate projects. Our team leverages innovative construction techniques to deliver exceptional properties that meet the evolving needs of our clients. SimpleAdvisory: As an SEC Registered Investment Advisor (RIA), SimpleAdvisory provides expert financial guidance and personalized investment strategies. We help our clients navigate the complexities of real estate investments with confidence and clarity. SimpleEquity: A private equity firm with a keen focus on equity investments, SimpleEquity partners with investors to identify and capitalize on lucrative opportunities in the real estate market. Our strategic approach ensures robust returns and long-term growth. SimpleMANAGE: This division manages our extensive portfolio of properties with a focus on efficiency, tenant satisfaction, and operational excellence. We provide comprehensive property management services that optimize asset performance and enhance tenant experiences. Our Vision:SimpleCiti Holdings strives to be a leader in the real estate industry by embracing simplicity, innovation, and excellence. We aim to create a seamless and enriching experience for our clients, tenants, and partners, fostering growth and success through our integrated approach. Our Values:
Simplicity: We believe in making complex processes simple and straightforward. Innovation: We embrace cutting-edge technologies and innovative solutions to stay ahead in the market. Excellence: We are committed to delivering the highest standards of quality and service in everything we do. Integrity: We conduct our business with honesty, transparency, and a strong sense of ethics. Collaboration: We value teamwork and partnership, working together to achieve shared goals. At SimpleCiti Holdings, we are redefining the real estate landscape, one simple solution at a time.

Work with a stable, growing company that values innovation and collaboration. Contribute to impactful projects alongside a team of accomplished technology professionals. Hybrid work model offering flexibility while fostering team synergy.

This is unique opportunity to help join a team where you'll be able to both build rapidly, and also contribute to product strategy and development!We are a highly collaborative team.

company_description:
Who are we?Berry Street is a business-in-a-box platform enabling registered dietitians to start and scale private practices that accept health insurance. We provide all of the software needed to run a thriving practice + administrative services like insurance contracting, eligibility verification, customer support, claims billing, and even patient acquisition. More about us:Americans' poor nutrition is killing us (and costing us billions). 3/4 are overweight
1/2 are obese
1/2 have 1+ chronic disease caused by poor nutrition
1 in 10 will have an eating disorder in their lifetime (binge eating, anorexia, bulimia, etc. )
Nutrition therapy is both clinically proven to make a difference and most commercial health insurance plans cover it at $0 out-of-pocket. We’re on a mission to fundamentally heal America’s relationship with food. Berry Street empowers registered dietitians to launch and grow in-network private practices. We’re creating game-changing technology to build America’s largest dietitian network and ensure that anyone can access the help they need. Since launching in January 2023, Berry Street has raised capital from top VCs like Village Global and angel investors like the founders of Elemy and Grow Therapy.

company_description: At AminoChain, our mission is to build the future of trust in science and healthcare, creating a world where patients are at the heart of biomedical research outcomes. We're developing the world's first decentralized protocol infrastructure for healthcare applications, connecting hospitals, biobanks, and bio-pharma companies to unlock the full potential of donated biological samples. Institutions joining our network by running a node become part of the "decentralized biobank. " This protocol powers various applications, including a bio-specimen marketplace, clinical trial recruitment, real-world data management via zero-knowledge proofs, decentralized AI, and federated learning. Looking ahead, our protocol will empower patients to track the use of their donated samples and data, provide personalized consent for broad research use, and participate in the value created from their contributions. This participation could take the form of patients and their communities receiving a share of the benefits through a DAO that manages a pool of collected donor fees to fund initiatives that matter the most to them. These automated features of transparency and benefit-sharing not only enable patient-centric governance models but also ensure that AminoChain ultimately gives agency and control back to the donors, fostering trust with individuals and communities who make research possible.

We provide all of the software needed to run a thriving practice + administrative services like insurance contracting, eligibility verification, customer support, claims billing, and even patient acquisition. More about us:Americans' poor nutrition is killing us (and costing us billions). 3/4 are overweight
1/2 are obese
1/2 have 1+ chronic disease caused by poor nutrition
1 in 10 will have an eating disorder in their lifetime (binge eating, anorexia, bulimia, etc. )
Nutrition therapy is both clinically proven to make a difference and most commercial health insurance plans cover it at $0 out-of-pocket. We’re on a mission to fundamentally heal America’s relationship with food. Berry Street empowers registered dietitians to launch and grow in-network private practices. We’re creating game-changing technology to build America’s largest dietitian network and ensure that anyone can access the help they need. Since launching in January 2023, Berry Street has raised capital from top VCs like Village Global and angel investors like the founders of Elemy and Grow Therapy.

You will work cross-functionally to evaluate opportunities, validate their impact at the organization, and build innovative solutions that support our patients, providers, and internal staff. What you'll do Zero-to-one feature development: Prove out AI feature ideas, iterate on them and integrate them into the product when they’re ready for prime time. Data curation and processing: Design the workflows and processes for gathering and storing data for model training. Model evaluation: Rigorously evaluate the performance of your work using whatever method is appropriate, from human preferences/labels to synthetic ground truth. Technical leadership: In this role you’ll have others looking to you for guidance on AI best practices and, more specifically, how to work with LLMs effectively.

company_description: At AminoChain, our mission is to build the future of trust in science and healthcare, creating a world where patients are at the heart of biomedical research outcomes. We're developing the world's first decentralized protocol infrastructure for healthcare applications, connecting hospitals, biobanks, and bio-pharma companies to unlock the full potential of donated biological samples. Institutions joining our network by running a node become part of the "decentralized biobank. " This protocol powers various applications, including a bio-specimen marketplace, clinical trial recruitment, real-world data management via zero-knowledge proofs, decentralized AI, and federated learning. Looking ahead, our protocol will empower patients to track the use of their donated samples and data, provide personalized consent for broad research use, and participate in the value created from their contributions. This participation could take the form of patients and their communities receiving a share of the benefits through a DAO that manages a pool of collected donor fees to fund initiatives that matter the most to them. These automated features of transparency and benefit-sharing not only enable patient-centric governance models but also ensure that AminoChain ultimately gives agency and control back to the donors, fostering trust with individuals and communities who make research possible.

We provide all of the software needed to run a thriving practice + administrative services like insurance contracting, eligibility verification, customer support, claims billing, and even patient acquisition. More about us:Americans' poor nutrition is killing us (and costing us billions). 3/4 are overweight
1/2 are obese
1/2 have 1+ chronic disease caused by poor nutrition
1 in 10 will have an eating disorder in their lifetime (binge eating, anorexia, bulimia, etc. )
Nutrition therapy is both clinically proven to make a difference and most commercial health insurance plans cover it at $0 out-of-pocket. We’re on a mission to fundamentally heal America’s relationship with food. Berry Street empowers registered dietitians to launch and grow in-network private practices. We’re creating game-changing technology to build America’s largest dietitian network and ensure that anyone can access the help they need. Since launching in January 2023, Berry Street has raised capital from top VCs like Village Global and angel investors like the founders of Elemy and Grow Therapy.

company_description: At AminoChain, our mission is to build the future of trust in science and healthcare, creating a world where patients are at the heart of biomedical research outcomes. We're developing the world's first decentralized protocol infrastructure for healthcare applications, connecting hospitals, biobanks, and bio-pharma companies to unlock the full potential of donated biological samples. Institutions joining our network by running a node become part of the "decentralized biobank. " This protocol powers various applications, including a bio-specimen marketplace, clinical trial recruitment, real-world data management via zero-knowledge proofs, decentralized AI, and federated learning. Looking ahead, our protocol will empower patients to track the use of their donated samples and data, provide personalized consent for broad research use, and participate in the value created from their contributions. This participation could take the form of patients and their communities receiving a share of the benefits through a DAO that manages a pool of collected donor fees to fund initiatives that matter the most to them. These automated features of transparency and benefit-sharing not only enable patient-centric governance models but also ensure that AminoChain ultimately gives agency and control back to the donors, fostering trust with individuals and communities who make research possible.

Who are we?Berry Street is a business-in-a-box platform enabling registered dietitians to start and scale private practices that accept health insurance. We provide all of the software needed to run a thriving practice + administrative services like insurance contracting, eligibility verification, customer support, claims billing, and even patient acquisition. More about us:Americans' poor nutrition is killing us (and costing us billions). 3/4 are overweight
1/2 are obese
1/2 have 1+ chronic disease caused by poor nutrition
1 in 10 will have an eating disorder in their lifetime (binge eating, anorexia, bulimia, etc. )
Nutrition therapy is both clinically proven to make a difference and most commercial health insurance plans cover it at $0 out-of-pocket. We’re on a mission to fundamentally heal America’s relationship with food. Berry Street empowers registered dietitians to launch and grow in-network private practices. We’re creating game-changing technology to build America’s largest dietitian network and ensure that anyone can access the help they need. Since launching in January 2023, Berry Street has raised capital from top VCs like Village Global and angel investors like the founders of Elemy and Grow Therapy.

company_description: At AminoChain, our mission is to build the future of trust in science and healthcare, creating a world where patients are at the heart of biomedical research outcomes. We're developing the world's first decentralized protocol infrastructure for healthcare applications, connecting hospitals, biobanks, and bio-pharma companies to unlock the full potential of donated biological samples. Institutions joining our network by running a node become part of the "decentralized biobank. " This protocol powers various applications, including a bio-specimen marketplace, clinical trial recruitment, real-world data management via zero-knowledge proofs, decentralized AI, and federated learning. Looking ahead, our protocol will empower patients to track the use of their donated samples and data, provide personalized consent for broad research use, and participate in the value created from their contributions. This participation could take the form of patients and their communities receiving a share of the benefits through a DAO that manages a pool of collected donor fees to fund initiatives that matter the most to them. These automated features of transparency and benefit-sharing not only enable patient-centric governance models but also ensure that AminoChain ultimately gives agency and control back to the donors, fostering trust with individuals and communities who make research possible.

We provide all of the software needed to run a thriving practice + administrative services like insurance contracting, eligibility verification, customer support, claims billing, and even patient acquisition. More about us:Americans' poor nutrition is killing us (and costing us billions). 3/4 are overweight
1/2 are obese
1/2 have 1+ chronic disease caused by poor nutrition
1 in 10 will have an eating disorder in their lifetime (binge eating, anorexia, bulimia, etc. )
Nutrition therapy is both clinically proven to make a difference and most commercial health insurance plans cover it at $0 out-of-pocket. We’re on a mission to fundamentally heal America’s relationship with food. Berry Street empowers registered dietitians to launch and grow in-network private practices. We’re creating game-changing technology to build America’s largest dietitian network and ensure that anyone can access the help they need. Since launching in January 2023, Berry Street has raised capital from top VCs like Village Global and angel investors like the founders of Elemy and Grow Therapy.

company_description: At AminoChain, our mission is to build the future of trust in science and healthcare, creating a world where patients are at the heart of biomedical research outcomes. We're developing the world's first decentralized protocol infrastructure for healthcare applications, connecting hospitals, biobanks, and bio-pharma companies to unlock the full potential of donated biological samples. Institutions joining our network by running a node become part of the "decentralized biobank. " This protocol powers various applications, including a bio-specimen marketplace, clinical trial recruitment, real-world data management via zero-knowledge proofs, decentralized AI, and federated learning. Looking ahead, our protocol will empower patients to track the use of their donated samples and data, provide personalized consent for broad research use, and participate in the value created from their contributions. This participation could take the form of patients and their communities receiving a share of the benefits through a DAO that manages a pool of collected donor fees to fund initiatives that matter the most to them. These automated features of transparency and benefit-sharing not only enable patient-centric governance models but also ensure that AminoChain ultimately gives agency and control back to the donors, fostering trust with individuals and communities who make research possible.

We provide all of the software needed to run a thriving practice + administrative services like insurance contracting, eligibility verification, customer support, claims billing, and even patient acquisition. More about us:Americans' poor nutrition is killing us (and costing us billions). 3/4 are overweight
1/2 are obese
1/2 have 1+ chronic disease caused by poor nutrition
1 in 10 will have an eating disorder in their lifetime (binge eating, anorexia, bulimia, etc. )

We’re creating game-changing technology to build America’s largest dietitian network and ensure that anyone can access the help they need. Since launching in January 2023, Berry Street has raised capital from top VCs like Village Global and angel investors like the founders of Elemy and Grow Therapy.

company_description: At AminoChain, our mission is to build the future of trust in science and healthcare, creating a world where patients are at the heart of biomedical research outcomes. We're developing the world's first decentralized protocol infrastructure for healthcare applications, connecting hospitals, biobanks, and bio-pharma companies to unlock the full potential of donated biological samples. Institutions joining our network by running a node become part of the "decentralized biobank. " This protocol powers various applications, including a bio-specimen marketplace, clinical trial recruitment, real-world data management via zero-knowledge proofs, decentralized AI, and federated learning. Looking ahead, our protocol will empower patients to track the use of their donated samples and data, provide personalized consent for broad research use, and participate in the value created from their contributions. This participation could take the form of patients and their communities receiving a share of the benefits through a DAO that manages a pool of collected donor fees to fund initiatives that matter the most to them. These automated features of transparency and benefit-sharing not only enable patient-centric governance models but also ensure that AminoChain ultimately gives agency and control back to the donors, fostering trust with individuals and communities who make research possible.
